Guild restrictions by Race
--------------------------

Guild restrictions by race are setup in the RACE_RESTRICT #define in the
guild header: guildd.h

The current moment (when this doc was written) the #define looks something
like this:

#define RACE_RESTRICT ([ \
"Barbarian" : ({}), \
"Bard" : ({ "ice ogre", }), \
"Charlatan" : ({ "barbarian", "high elf", "silver elf", "stone dwarf", }), \
  .
  .
  . 
"Smith" : ({ }), \
"Thief" : ({ "desert dwarf", "stone dwarf", "barbarian" }) \
])

The keys to the mapping are the string names of the guilds. Each value
associated with a key is an string array player race names. The array
specifies the races that are NOT allowed to join the guild. Thus any
race can join the "Smith" guild, and only "ice ogre"s are disallowed
from joining bards. These restrictions have very little to do with
whether the race/guild is a good fit or not.
 
Race/guild restrictions should ONLY be checked when actually joining
the guild or switching race, not in any other guild code. Adding/removing
restrictions should not affect people already in the guild.

Every guild should be added as a key into this mapping, even if the
race list is empty. Guild coders can modify the restriction list simply
by adding/removing items from the race array for their guild.

